  , issueBody =
      Just
        "Can anyone explain why one query inside database slower than two queries in runtime? I have table 'folder' , table 'boards' with 'folders_id' index and table 'posts' with 'boards_id' index. My first query \r\n```javascript\r\nr.connect(config.rethinkdb).then(dbConn=>{\r\n  var time = Date.now();\r\n  r.table('boards').getAll('1233131', {index: 'folders_id'}).concatMap(board=>{\r\n    return r.table('posts').getAll(board('id'),{index: 'boards_id'})\r\n  }).coerceTo('array').run(dbConn).then((res)=>{\r\n    console.log(Date.now()-time, res.length);\r\n  });\r\n});\r\n```\r\nuses concatMap and it took nearly 151 ms. But secon query \r\n```javascript\r\n\r\nr.connect(config.rethinkdb).then(dbConn=>{\r\n  var time = Date.now();\r\n  r.table('boards').getAll('1233131', {index: 'folders_id'}).map(r.row('id')).coerceTo('array').run(dbConn).then(ids=>{\r\n    console.log(Date.now()-time, ids.length);\r\n    var arr = ids;\r\n    arr.push({index: 'boards_id'});\r\n    var thisObj = r.table('posts');\r\n    return thisObj.getAll.apply(thisObj, arr).coerceTo('array').run(dbConn)\r\n  }).then((res)=>{\r\n    console.log(Date.now()-time, res.length);\r\n  });\r\n});\r\n```\r\nuses two runtime queries (first retrieves all ids and second fetches all posts) and it took nearly 60 ms. I tested with other data and concatMap approach twice (or three times on small data) slower then approach with retrieves ids and then items itself"
